880:The iter-033 result intentionally does \emph{not} touch the universe bridge to $\HModule$ — that final piece (which involves upgrading Mathlib's $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUniv} : \Ext_w\,X\,Y\,n \cong \Ext_{w'}\,X\,Y\,n$ from a bare $\Equiv$ to a $\LinearEquiv$, plus composition with iter-032's $\HModule\,\mathtt{\_top\_linearEquiv}$) is iter-034+ work. By splitting Step 3 into a cover-totality piece (iter-031/032/033) plus a universe-bump piece (iter-034+), each iteration appends one declaration.
903:\subsection{Universe-bump and full cover-totality bridge (iter-034)}
909:\begin{definition}[Universe-bump $\LinearEquiv$ — Mathlib gap-fill, iter-034]
910:  \label{def:Abelian_Ext_chgUnivLinearEquiv}
911:  \lean{CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext.chgUnivLinearEquiv}
922:  The underlying bijection is Mathlib's $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUniv}$. To prove additivity, fix the standard derived-category instance $\mathtt{HasDerivedCategory.standard}\,C$ and apply $\Ext.\mathtt{ext}$ (homomorphism injectivity through $\mathtt{homEquiv}$). The goal becomes $\mathtt{homEquiv}\,(\mathtt{chgUniv}\,(a+b)) = \mathtt{homEquiv}\,(\mathtt{chgUniv}\,a) + \mathtt{homEquiv}\,(\mathtt{chgUniv}\,b)$; using $\Ext.\mathtt{add\_hom}$ on both sides reduces to $\mathtt{homEquiv}\,(\mathtt{chgUniv}\,(a+b)) = \mathtt{homEquiv}\,(a+b)$ (and similarly for the summands), which is exactly $\Ext.\mathtt{homEquiv\_chgUniv}$ applied three times. The $R$-linearity proof is identical with $\Ext.\mathtt{smul\_hom}$ in place of $\Ext.\mathtt{add\_hom}$. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-034 pass) confirms both helper lemmas plus the bundled $\LinearEquiv$ structure literal typecheck end-to-end and produce kernel-only axioms.
925:\begin{definition}[Full cover-totality bridge $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ for terminal $T$, iter-034]
926:  \label{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_eq_HModule_linearEquiv}
927:  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_eq_HModule_linearEquiv}
928:  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_top_linearEquiv, def:Abelian_Ext_chgUnivLinearEquiv, def:Scheme_HModule, def:Scheme_HModule_prime}
940:  Compose iter-033's $\HModulePrimeTopLinearEquiv$ (which lands on $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n$ for $X_2 = (\constantSheaf\,J\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k)$) with the universe-bump $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUnivLinearEquiv}$ from Definition~\ref{def:Abelian_Ext_chgUnivLinearEquiv} (which lifts $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n$ to $\Ext_{u+1}\,X_2\,F\,n$). By definition (iter-009), $\HModule\,k\,F\,n = \Ext_{u+1}\,X_2\,F\,n$, so the composition yields the desired $\LinearEquiv$. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-034 pass) confirms the one-liner $(\HModulePrimeTopLinearEquiv\,k\,F\,n\,h_T).\mathtt{trans}\,\Ext.\mathtt{chgUnivLinearEquiv}$ typechecks and produces kernel-only axioms. Both $\HasExt_u$ and $\HasExt_{u+1}$ must be passed as explicit hypotheses (typeclass synthesis from $\HasSheafify$ alone times out on the underlying $\HasSmallLocalizedHom$ chain at 20\,000 heartbeats).
945:The iter-029 lemmas materialise Step 1 (the abstract LES) and Step 2 (the corner-identification simp lemmas) of the iter-028 Serre-finiteness sketch (Section~\ref{sec:scheme_affineCoverMVSquare}); iter-030 materialised Step 2.5 (the toModuleKSheaf specialisation, a routine binding so downstream code paths can reference the LES on the structure sheaf of a curve directly); iter-031 materialised the \emph{source-object} half of Step 3 (the cover-totality identification at the sheaf level); iter-032 materialised the \emph{Ext-transport} half of Step 3 at universe $u+1$ (landing on $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$); iter-033 materialised the parallel \emph{Ext-transport} at universe $u$ (landing on $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n$); iter-034 (this iteration) closes Step 3 by appending the Mathlib gap-fill $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUnivLinearEquiv}$ (universe-bump $\LinearEquiv$ upgrade of Mathlib's bare $\Equiv$ $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUniv}$) and composing iter-033 with it to produce the full bridge $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ for terminal $T$. The remaining work — Step 4 (affine vanishing $H^{>0}(\Spec A, \mathcal F) = 0$, possibly multi-iteration depending on Mathlib state) and Step 5 (finiteness of each $H^0$ piece, hence of $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$) — is iter-035+. The intermediate iter-035 step (specialise to $\AffineCoverMVSquare$ via iter-029's $\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare\_toSquare\_X_4} : \ldots = \top$ simp lemma to land the bridge on the $X_4$ corner of an affine cover) is plausibly single-iteration $\sim$10–20 LOC.

